        <mxCell id="gqyGLWo6HeyIAnXtJu5Z-68" parent="1" style="shape=callout;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;perimeter=calloutPerimeter;fillColor=#60a917;fontColor=#ffffff;strokeColor=#2D7600;" value="This architecture we separated the dependency, we can add events to Rach extensions without breaking other extensions, we can add new VCs with it&#39;s extensions without breaking the dependencies&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;we can test thing independently, we can have multiple developers working in the same modules without conflicts, you can have the abstractions from VCs from implementation of the engines which means we can swap engines easily,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="220" width="450" x="1070" y="1100" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="gqyGLWo6HeyIAnXtJu5Z-69" parent="1" style="shape=callout;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;perimeter=calloutPerimeter;fillColor=#e51400;fontColor=#ffffff;strokeColor=#B20000;" value="&lt;div&gt;The downsides:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;-name Collisions which lead to prefixing method names with something and force other to follow the role ex:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;for all login methods we should prefix with&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- loginVC_loginScreenViewed()&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;-loginVC_loginAttempted()&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;but still struct base approach better than enum based because it enables you to easily create modules and it can add more behaviours without breaking old behavious&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;you wanna be able to extend without without having to change code&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;if you have good architecture your code is resilient and this is the &#39;O&#39; in the Solid principles, open/close principle : the code is open for extension and closed for modifications&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;but also we can say enums and structs are too concrete let&#39;s use a protocol instead of them&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="320" width="450" x="1580" y="1100" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
